{"TopicId":206867,"ForumId":44,"TopicTitle":"Three legs or four?","CreatedByName":"boriz","CreatedById":219053,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-02-11T21:36:37Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"boriz","CreatedById":219053,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-02-11T21:36:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have often wondered why the Apollo 11 LEM had four legs and not three. I\u0027m sure that an extra unnecessary leg would represent extra unnecessary mass, and three legs would be better when landing on uneven terrain. So why the extra leg?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Randazzo","CreatedById":136468,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-02-11T22:01:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224090509\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022206867\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221644615397\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022219053\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022boriz\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n20 minutes ago, boriz said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have often wondered why the Apollo 11 LEM had four legs and not three. I\u0027m sure that an extra unnecessary leg would represent extra unnecessary mass, and three legs would be better when landing on uneven terrain. So why the extra leg?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStability and safety. I think they started with five.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Beamer","CreatedById":219034,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-02-12T01:40:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlthough 3 fixed legs are inherently stable on an uneven surface, springs/dampeners can adjust for that, and 4 legs give you a greater distance between center of gravity and turning point which means you can stand on steeper inclines without tipping over - and perhaps crucially, land with a greater horizontal speed without tipping over.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTo prevent tipping, assuming a circular limited space (like a rocket fairing) the more legs the better, but there are diminishing returns w.r.t. tipping the more legs you add, and of course there are weight considerations. Even though more legs mean each leg can be lighter, presumably there is some overhead that adds up (although being able to design legs to specification rather than having to choose between a couple of prefab models like in KSP helps \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E )\u003C/span\u003E. The tipping point difference between 3 and 4 is quite big though so I guess 4 was the acceptable trade-off they came up with between those considerations.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Snark","CreatedById":125662,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-02-12T02:31:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMoving to Science \u0026amp;\u00A0 Spaceflight, since this is about IRL spaceflight rather than KSP.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(Though you could verify this issue yourself in KSP, if you wanted to, by trying some landings on the Mun, on rugged terrain, and see the difference it makes in terms of how easy it is to tip over...) \u003Cimg alt=\u0022;)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-02-12T04:52:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFour is too few.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSmart guys have six.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022landing-gear.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002271.60\u0022 height=\u0022358\u0022 width=\u0022500\u0022 src=\u0022https://falsesteps.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/landing-gear.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf one fails, five stand.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"mikegarrison","CreatedById":137807,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-02-12T08:37:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat is a consideration. Four legs is one more point of failure, and yet adds no redundancy because the remaining three legs do not create a stable base.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"magnemoe","CreatedById":57801,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-02-12T13:41:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224090682\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022206867\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221644655074\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022137807\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022mikegarrison\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, mikegarrison said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat is a consideration. Four legs is one more point of failure, and yet adds no redundancy because the remaining three legs do not create a stable base.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAn point however a leg main fail point is the suspension or folding mechanism. If the leg snaps off at the mounting points you are likely to have more serious problems.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\nSo if you design this a bit smart you still has an semi usable leg.\u003Cbr\u003E\nI assume the main reason is an wider base,as Snark said above. 3 legs are self stabilizing but the base is not very big compared to distance between feet. 4 is much better and its an dimishing return with 5 or 6 legs.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Aerodynamic Kerbal","CreatedById":211338,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-02-12T14:29:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224090641\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022206867\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221644641555\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 hours ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFour is too few.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSmart guys have six.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022#\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/a\u003E \u003Cspan\u003EHide contents\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://falsesteps.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/landing-gear.jpg\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022landing-gear.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u002271.60\u0022 height=\u0022358\u0022 width=\u0022500\u0022 src=\u0022https://falsesteps.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/landing-gear.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf one fails, five stand.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSmort guys have infinite\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022starship3.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022150.00\u0022 height=\u00221200\u0022 width=\u0022800\u0022 src=\u0022https://spaceflightnow.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/starship3.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-02-12T14:53:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224090756\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022206867\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221644676181\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022211338\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Aerodynamic Kerbal\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n21 minutes ago, Aerodynamic Kerbal said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSmort guys have infinite\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSmart guys use legs instead of catching a rocket by armpits.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nazalassa","CreatedById":217956,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-02-12T15:30:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nVery smart guys think \u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cem\u003Elanding legs are overrated\u003C/em\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E and use \u003Cu\u003Eengine noozles\u003C/u\u003E instead to save weight and part count in Career.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-02-12T15:38:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224090773\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022206867\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221644679833\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022217956\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Nazalassa\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 minutes ago, Nazalassa said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nVery smart guys think \u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cem\u003Elanding legs are overrated\u003C/em\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E and use \u003Cu\u003Eengine noozles\u003C/u\u003E instead to save weight and part count in Career.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOn landing any nozzle is unburnt metal fuel.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nazalassa","CreatedById":217956,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-02-12T15:39:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224090776\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022206867\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221644680304\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOn landing any nozzle is unburnt metal fuel.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHahaha yes \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"StrandedonEarth","CreatedById":89439,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-02-12T17:41:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf three legs was \u201Cstable enough,\u201D then 3-wheel ATVs would still be for sale new\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"magnemoe","CreatedById":57801,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-02-12T18:27:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224090822\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022206867\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221644687678\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002289439\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022StrandedonEarth\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 minutes ago, StrandedonEarth said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf three legs was \u201Cstable enough,\u201D then 3-wheel ATVs would still be for sale new\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStory is a bit more complex I think as lots of them was used by kids,\u00A0 obvious benefit of 3 wheels is\u00A0 that you can use an simple bicycle handlebar rather than the more complex control needed for four wheels.\u00A0\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.motorbiscuit.com/theres-a-very-good-reason-you-dont-see-3-wheeled-atvs-anymore/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.motorbiscuit.com/theres-a-very-good-reason-you-dont-see-3-wheeled-atvs-anymore/\u003C/a\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nAs an bonus I got an add from the site, the ultimate fake meme tank is now an Lego model.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://theblockzone.com/products/missile-carrier-tank-3665pcs?variant=8103616315489\u0026amp;currency=GBP\u0026amp;utm_medium=product_sync\u0026amp;utm_source=google\u0026amp;utm_content=sag_organic\u0026amp;utm_campaign=sag_organic\u0026amp;gclid=EAIaIQobChMI7-bsj9769QIVbdIRCB3cnw6EEAEYASACEgIzjPD_BwE\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://theblockzone.com/products/missile-carrier-tank-3665pcs?variant=8103616315489\u0026amp;currency=GBP\u0026amp;utm_medium=product_sync\u0026amp;utm_source=google\u0026amp;utm_content=sag_organic\u0026amp;utm_campaign=sag_organic\u0026amp;gclid=EAIaIQobChMI7-bsj9769QIVbdIRCB3cnw6EEAEYASACEgIzjPD_BwE\u003C/a\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nNo the original design had an\u00A0Katyusha rocket launcher rather than the two huge ones but still had the feature that the large gun would hit the small one firing straight forward.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\nIt don\u0027t look like its an model you can drive, other crafts come with an remote control and listing of motors like tanks or cranes.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-02-12T18:43:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt works in KSP, why shouldn\u0027t irl.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://spacedock.info/mod/1905/Reliant%20Robin\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://spacedock.info/mod/1905/Reliant Robin\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022113\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022 data-embed-src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/mJ4KuvHbqjs?feature=oembed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022113\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022 data-embed-src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/xVdA27at02w?feature=oembed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"StrandedonEarth","CreatedById":89439,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-02-12T19:08:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224090839\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022206867\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221644690458\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257801\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022magnemoe\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n36 minutes ago, magnemoe said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStory is a bit more complex I think as lots of them was used by kids,\u00A0 obvious benefit of 3 wheels is\u00A0 that you can use an simple bicycle handlebar rather than the more complex control needed for four wheels.\u00A0\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.motorbiscuit.com/theres-a-very-good-reason-you-dont-see-3-wheeled-atvs-anymore/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.motorbiscuit.com/theres-a-very-good-reason-you-dont-see-3-wheeled-atvs-anymore/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks for that, I should have realized the dynamics of a ATC would be different than a non-wheeled lander. Still, if redundancy is valued over mass, then five would probably be best, with plenty of suspension travel.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"wumpus","CreatedById":133850,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-02-12T23:25:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224090839\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022206867\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221644690458\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257801\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022magnemoe\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, magnemoe said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStory is a bit more complex I think as lots of them was used by kids,\u00A0 obvious benefit of 3 wheels is\u00A0 that you can use an simple bicycle handlebar rather than the more complex control needed for four wheels.\u00A0\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.motorbiscuit.com/theres-a-very-good-reason-you-dont-see-3-wheeled-atvs-anymore/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.motorbiscuit.com/theres-a-very-good-reason-you-dont-see-3-wheeled-atvs-anymore/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere\u0027s also the issue that you get much better stability on a 3-wheeled vehicle if you put 2 wheels up front and 1 behind.\u00A0 The Polaris Slingshot comes to mind as an example, as well as Buckminster Fuller\u0027s\u00A0Dymaxion car (I thought Polaris made a much higher \u0022motocyclish\u0022 2-wheels in front trike, but can\u0027t find it).\u00A0 You are vastly more likely to be decelerating while turning than accelerating while turning, so you want your wheels ahead and to the sides.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SunlitZelkova","CreatedById":206402,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-02-13T01:42:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224090509\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022206867\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221644615397\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022219053\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022boriz\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 2/11/2022 at 1:36 PM, boriz said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have often wondered why the Apollo 11 LEM had four legs and not three. I\u0027m sure that an extra unnecessary leg would represent extra unnecessary mass, and three legs would be better when landing on uneven terrain. So why the extra leg?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://space.stackexchange.com/questions/13501/why-did-the-apollo-lunar-module-have-four-landing-legs#:~:text=In%20particular%2C%20chapter%206.4%20notes,during%201963%2C%20decided%20on%20four.\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://space.stackexchange.com/questions/13501/why-did-the-apollo-lunar-module-have-four-landing-legs#:~:text=In particular%2C chapter 6.4 notes,during 1963%2C decided on four.\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTwo quotes from this that answer the question-\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nQuote\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGrumman had first considered five legs but, during 1963, decided on four. The change was dictated by the weight-versus-strength tradeoff that had produced the cruciform descent stage, with its four obvious attachment points. The revised gear pattern also greatly simplified the structural mounting of the vehicle within the adapter.\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cem\u003E \u003C/em\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cu\u003E\u003Cem\u003EFour legs set on the orthogonal axes of the lander (forward, aft, left, and right) mated ideally with the pattern of four reaction control \u0022quads\u0022 (the basic four-engine package).\u003C/em\u003E\u003C/u\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E The quads were rotated 45 degrees so the downward-thrusting attitude control engine fired between the two nearest gear legs, overcoming a severe thermal problem of the five-leg arrangement.\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nQuote\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, a three-legged design would\u0027ve had a significantly smaller stability margin when landing on a slope, and/or if any residual horizontal velocity remained while landing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222022-02-13T01:42:39Z\u0022 title=\u002202/13/2022 01:42  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 13, 2022\u003C/time\u003E by SunlitZelkova\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"NFUN","CreatedById":78715,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-02-13T03:07:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthree legs good, four legs better\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224090848\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022206867\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221644691389\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 hours ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt works in KSP, why shouldn\u0027t irl.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://spacedock.info/mod/1905/Reliant%20Robin\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://spacedock.info/mod/1905/Reliant Robin\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022#\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/a\u003E \u003Cspan\u003EHide contents\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022113\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022 data-embed-src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/mJ4KuvHbqjs?feature=oembed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022113\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022 data-embed-src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/xVdA27at02w?feature=oembed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nuh, do you know why they modded that into ksp?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-02-13T06:31:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224090964\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022206867\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221644721655\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002278715\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022NFUN\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, NFUN said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ndo you know why they modded that into ksp?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey wanted something three-wheeled?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224090964\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022206867\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221644721655\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002278715\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022NFUN\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, NFUN said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthree legs good, four legs better\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe Pierson\u0027s Puppeteers aren\u0027t agreed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Pierson\u0027s_Puppeteer_illustration_from_Ba\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022159.20\u0022 height=\u0022398\u0022 width=\u0022250\u0022 src=\u0022https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/2/20/Pierson\u0027s_Puppeteer_illustration_from_Barlowe\u0027s_Guide_to_Extraterrestrials.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"NFUN","CreatedById":78715,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-02-13T17:57:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224091033\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022206867\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221644733919\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 hours ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey wanted something three-wheeled?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe Pierson\u0027s Puppeteers aren\u0027t agreed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022#\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/a\u003E \u003Cspan\u003EReveal hidden contents\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/2/20/Pierson\u0027s_Puppeteer_illustration_from_Barlowe\u0027s_Guide_to_Extraterrestrials.jpg\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Pierson\u0027s_Puppeteer_illustration_from_Ba\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022159.20\u0022 height=\u0022398\u0022 width=\u0022250\u0022 src=\u0022https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/2/20/Pierson\u0027s_Puppeteer_illustration_from_Barlowe\u0027s_Guide_to_Extraterrestrials.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nbecause somebody\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Ealready did it IRL\u003C/em\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://youtube.com/watch?v=pJdrlWR-yFM\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://youtube.com/watch?v=pJdrlWR-yFM\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222022-02-13T17:57:48Z\u0022 title=\u002202/13/2022 05:57  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 13, 2022\u003C/time\u003E by NFUN\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-02-13T18:47:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224091300\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022206867\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221644775049\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002278715\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022NFUN\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n47 minutes ago, NFUN said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nbecause somebody\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Ealready did it IRL\u003C/em\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd not once.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Three-wheeler\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Three-wheeler\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Beamer","CreatedById":219034,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-02-15T15:17:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224091033\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022206867\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221644733919\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 2/13/2022 at 7:31 AM, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey wanted something three-wheeled?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe Pierson\u0027s Puppeteers aren\u0027t agreed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022#\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/a\u003E \u003Cspan\u003EHide contents\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/2/20/Pierson\u0027s_Puppeteer_illustration_from_Barlowe\u0027s_Guide_to_Extraterrestrials.jpg\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Pierson\u0027s_Puppeteer_illustration_from_Ba\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022159.20\u0022 height=\u0022398\u0022 width=\u0022250\u0022 src=\u0022https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/2/20/Pierson\u0027s_Puppeteer_illustration_from_Barlowe\u0027s_Guide_to_Extraterrestrials.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe the lack of a 4th leg is why they were such scaredy-cats though \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E. I love Niven, but as useful as a 3-legged design is for a picnic table, it is a pretty bad layout for an ambulatory creature, and assuming growth by cell division probably extremely unlikely to evolve without \u0027help\u0027 by some designer of sorts. It was on Earth anyway. Even the artist of that picture seems to have had trouble with it, as that hind leg looks like it has a double femur, suggesting it started off as a 4-legged creature where the hind legs fused together during its development.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-02-15T15:30:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI guess, he was writing them from a home theater for children, with sweater on the head and a stool as the rear leg.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"magnemoe","CreatedById":57801,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-02-15T23:23:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224090918\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022206867\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221644708358\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022133850\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022wumpus\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 2/13/2022 at 12:25 AM, wumpus said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere\u0027s also the issue that you get much better stability on a 3-wheeled vehicle if you put 2 wheels up front and 1 behind.\u00A0 The Polaris Slingshot comes to mind as an example, as well as Buckminster Fuller\u0027s\u00A0Dymaxion car (I thought Polaris made a much higher \u0022motocyclish\u0022 2-wheels in front trike, but can\u0027t find it).\u00A0 You are vastly more likely to be decelerating while turning than accelerating while turning, so you want your wheels ahead and to the sides.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTrue not only braking and turning but just turning sharply off road and its an risk the front wheel hit something or dig in. Downside is that\u00A0 2 front wheels kills the simple bicycle steering cost saving,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}